eventData.headline: Taps at Yale
eventData.description:
Taps at Yale, Yale's best and only all-tap dance student organization, was founded in 1995. A professional-level company, Taps is a dynamic group dedicated to performing and spreading our love of tap dancing. Every year, Taps produces two student-choreographed performances, showcasing the incredible range of styles within the art form. Dance abilities range from "I haven't tapped since I was 4" to "I played Billy Elliot on Broadway.” All are welcome to audition. Please visit https://tapsatyale.wixsite.com/yale for more information.

Come to Taps at Yale's info session! Meet current members of Taps, ask questions, and watch videos of past Taps performances.

eventData.headline: Red Hot Poker
eventData.description:
Red Hot Poker is Yale's funniest and hottest sketch comedy group. We meet twice a week for a "writers room," where we pitch and workshop our sketches. And we put on several well-attended shows a semester! We hold an annual audition in September.

Come see comedic sketches and talk with the group!

eventData.headline: Men's Club Soccer
eventData.description:
FCYU is Yale’s top level of men’s club soccer. We compete yearly in three fall competitions: the New England Collegiate Club Soccer League (NECCSL), the Ivy League Club Soccer Tournament, and the Northeast Regional Club Soccer Tournament. We also enter teams in winter indoor leagues in Hamden, CT and play friendly matches throughout the academic year against club and varsity teams from neighbouring colleges.

Join us for an information session on FCYU.

eventData.headline: First Year Outdoor Orientation (FOOT)
eventData.description:
We invite you to join us for an experience that many students say is one of the most formative and important of their time at Yale. On FOOT, you will sleep under the stars, share stories and songs around the campfire, create a new tight-knit community of friends, enjoy discovering the Northeastern landscape, and spend time discussing what life at Yale will be like.

Come learn about FOOT! Leaders from all class years will be present to answer any questions. We'll play some classic FOOT games and get to know each other a bit!

eventData.headline: The Opera Theater of Yale College
eventData.description:
The event is a short info session from 5:30-6:00, followed by two open rehearsals from 6:00-7:00pm. The first, from 6:00-6:30pm will be for our upcoming William Grant Still song gala, and the second, from 6:30-7:00 will be for our upcoming production of an opera by Ben Beckman '23.5, called "Basement Among the Stars".

The Opera Theater of Yale College, Yale’s only student-run undergraduate opera organization, is now in its twenty-first season. Founded in the fall of 1998, its initial production of Handel’s Julius Caesar, which was fully-staged and sung in Italian, drew great critical acclaim. Since, OTYC has expanded and grown.

OTYC is entirely student-run, and designed to provide undergraduates at Yale College with opportunities to choose repertoire, produce, direct, design, and perform. Our members are singers, instrumentalists, conductors, theatre technicians, costume and set designers, choreographers, and dancers. OTYC is governed by a board of students who have varying backgrounds and experiences, but who are committed to making opera fun and accessible to everyone.

Our seasons reflect our growing organization. We perform around four operas each academic year, three of which are accompanied by an orchestra with full set and costume. Our repertoire spans a wide range of languages and styles, from baroque to contemporary.
We are committed to bringing creative, thoughtful, and innovative opera productions to the Yale and New Haven communities. We look forward to seeing you at our upcoming performances!

eventData.headline: Yale Club Synchronized Swimming
eventData.description:
Undergraduates from all experience levels who come together to learn synchronized swimming. A fun combination of swimming and dance! Open to anyone who wants to learn.  We compete, hang out, and are not super high commitment and only practice ~2/week.

Come hang out and listen to some tunes and meet some of our current members! Learn about fun synchro skills, what the team is like, and even see some of our videos/competition pictures! We'd love to meet you! :)

eventData.headline: Splash at Yale
eventData.description:
Splash at Yale is an event that brings high school and middle school students to Yale University for one day of unlimited learning. Students who come take class in a variety of both conventional and unconventional subjects taught by Yale undergraduate and graduate students! [Due to the ongoing pandemic, we will be hosting an online program this spring.]

Learn about our awesome organization and meet some of our current admins!
